commit f05bdac2cf28a42c3858b0f2ebedcbbe7b6639ba
Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 3 14:22:01 2026 +0200

    fix(mcp-server): analytics + learning remediation — PII redaction, pricing single-source, boost math
    
    Three approved Tier-2 backlog remediations (gpt-5.5-fast confirmed; implemented + tested).
    
    1. PRIVACY — consumption_log.query_text held raw agent-prompt text (241 live rows).
       Column becomes query_hash storing a truncate+hash fingerprint (8 chars + sha256
       prefix), computed before any SQL. Lazy self-migration drops the old-schema table
       on init (rows are disposable telemetry; the drop IS the PII elimination) and the
       3 handler callers + all readers (frequency group-by, intent-mismatch) key on the
       hash. Live 241 rows are erased when the daemon next recycles + migrates.
    
    2. PRICING — removed the dead model_pricing_versioned DB table + seed + listModelPricing
       (zero non-test callers); the hardcoded SEEDED_MODEL_PRICING_ROWS is now the documented
       single source of family-level pricing for internal analytics.
    
    3. BATCH-LEARNING — boost divided by event count (per-event average), so the cap was a
       no-op and 3 vs 300 sessions gave identical boost. Add SCORE_NORMALIZATION=10.0 so boost
       scales with volume: min((weightedScore/10)*0.10, 0.10). Shadow-only (dashboards, not
       live ranking).
    
    Packet 011-analytics-and-learning-remediation validates --strict 0/0. typecheck clean;
    103 tests pass across the 4 suites (incl. 9 new privacy tests + a volume-scaling test).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

